  "summary": "Malicious code in node-sysmon-native (npm)",
  "details": "Node-sysmon-native@1.0.0 is a trojanized native addon that masquerades as a system-monitoring package. On install, node-gyp rebuild compiles sysmon[.]cc, which contains an XOR-encoded C2 URL. When the module is required, it spawns a detached pthread that loops fetching commands from the C2 server's /cmd/commands endpoint, executes them via bash -c, and posts the output to /cmd/results. The C2 server is at 152[.]53[.]120[.]90. The package has no repository and its sole purpose is to establish a remote shell on the installer's machine.",
